setUpGAParameters

private static org.jgap.Configuration setUpGAParameters(int populationSize)
                                                 throws org.jgap.InvalidConfigurationException
Set up GA parameters: Default configuration, fitness function as determined by ImproviserCreativityFitnessFunction, population Size as set by the parameter, a sample Chromosome to be used as templates for all Chromosomes in the GA that contains 10 genes: PolyphonyGene, MaxNumNotesGene, KeyGene, NoteRangeGene, LowestNoteGene, RhythmMultiplierGene, NoteRestRatioGene, NumImprovisationsGene, medianTempoGene, maxTempoGene NB all genes are given an appropriate range of values, as set in the global variables for this class

Parameters:
populationSize - the population Size for the GA
Returns:
a default [org.jgap.]Configuration: set of parameters for a jGap Genetic Algorithm
Throws:
org.jgap.InvalidConfigurationException

generateFinalRepresentativeImpro

private static void generateFinalRepresentativeImpro(org.jgap.IChromosome chromosome,
                                                     java.lang.Integer polyphony,
                                                     java.lang.Integer maxNotesToGenerate,
                                                     java.lang.Integer key,
                                                     java.lang.Integer noteRange,
                                                     java.lang.Integer lowestNote,
                                                     java.lang.Integer rhythmMult,
                                                     java.lang.Integer noteRestRatio,
                                                     java.lang.Integer medianTempo,
                                                     java.lang.Integer tempoVariance)
Generates a representative sample of the improvisations by an individual in the population

Parameters:
chromosome - chromosome representing the individual in the population
polyphony - the number of voices in the improv sample
maxNotesToGenerate - the max number of notes to be generated in the improv sample
key - the key of the improv sample
noteRange - the range of notes to be used in the improv sample (as no. of notes above the lowestNote)
lowestNote - the lowest note that could be used in the improv sample (as midi value)
rhythmMult - divisive factor representing the length of the shortest notes possible in the improv sample
noteRestRatio - ratio of notes to rests in the improv sample
medianTempo - the tempo of the improv sample (which may be affected by the tempoVariance parameter)
tempoVariance - the amount by which the medianTempo can be varied as the tempo for the improv sample
